article.headline: Texas-Arlington 76, Texas-Pan American 51
article.story: EDINBURG, Texas -- Marquez Haynes scored 16 points and Texas-Arlington defeated Texas-Pan American 76-51 Wednesday night. Tommy Moffitt came off the bench to score 15 points. Brandon Long scored 13 and Roge'r Guignard added 12 for Texas-Arlington (7-6). Haynes, Moffitt and Anthony Vereen each had eight rebounds. Emmanuel Jones led Texas-Pan American (5-10) with 13 points while Nick Weiermiller added 12, all from 3-pointers. Texas-Arlington scored the first six points of the game before Texas-Pan American's Jason Jensen hit a jumper with 15:30 to go in the first half. Texas-Pan American closed to within three points late in the first half before Texas-Arlington took control by holding the Broncos scoreless over a seven-minute span that stretched early into the second half.
